    "text": "STATEMENT OF WORK\nProfessional Services Agreement\n\nContract Number: SOW-2024-001\nEffective Date: January 1, 2024\nExpiration Date: December 31, 2024\nTotal Contract Value: $750,000 USD\n\nPARTIES:\nClient: TechCorp Inc.\nAddress: 123 Technology Drive, San Francisco, CA 94105\nContact: John Smith, VP of Technology\n\nService Provider: Digital Solutions LLC\nAddress: 456 Innovation Boulevard, Austin, TX 78701\nContact: Sarah Johnson, Managing Director\n\nSCOPE OF WORK:\nThis Statement of Work outlines professional services for digital transformation platform development including:\n- System architecture design and implementation\n- Application development and testing\n- Data migration and integration services\n- User training and change management\n- Post-implementation support and maintenance\n\nPAYMENT SCHEDULE:\nTotal contract value: $750,000 USD payable as follows:\n- Project Kickoff: $187,500 (25%) - Due: January 15, 2024\n- Phase 1 Completion: $187,500 (25%) - Due: April 15, 2024\n- Phase 2 Completion: $187,500 (25%) - Due: July 15, 2024\n- Final Delivery: $187,500 (25%) - Due: October 15, 2024\n\nEXPENSE BREAKDOWN:\n- Professional Services: $525,000 (70%)\n- Travel & Expenses: $112,500 (15%)\n- Software Licenses: $75,000 (10%)\n- Contingency: $37,500 (5%)\n\nPROFESSIONAL SERVICES RATE CARD:\nEffective Date: January 1, 2024 | Currency: USD\n- Senior Consultant: $175/hr ($1,400/day) - Consulting\n- Project Manager: $150/hr ($1,200/day) - Management\n- Business Analyst: $125/hr ($1,000/day) - Analysis\n- Senior Developer: $140/hr ($1,120/day) - Development\n- Developer: $110/hr ($880/day) - Development\n- QA Engineer: $115/hr ($920/day) - Quality Assurance\n- Technical Architect: $195/hr ($1,560/day) - Architecture\n- Data Analyst: $120/hr ($960/day) - Analysis\n- UX Designer: $130/hr ($1,040/day) - Design\n- DevOps Engineer: $165/hr ($1,320/day) - Operations\n\nTERMS:\nPayment Terms: Net 30 days from invoice date\nLate Payment Penalties: 1.5% per month compounded monthly\nTermination: Either party may terminate with 30 days written notice\nLiability: Service Provider's liability limited to total contract value\nGoverning Law: State of California\nCompliance: SOX and GDPR compliant",
